{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"760f4e92-18ec-4a09-b41f-24928b275c93","content":"I can help guide you on analyzing your .NET crash dump. Here are your main options:\n\n**1. `dotnet-dump analyze`** (cross-platform):\n```bash\ndotnet tool install -g dotnet-dump\ndotnet-dump analyze your-file.dmp\n```\nUseful commands inside the analyzer:\n- `clrstack` – managed call stack\n- `pe` – print last exception\n- `dumpheap -stat` – heap summary\n- `threads` – list all threads\n\n**2. WinDbg** (Windows, full-featured):\n- Load the dump, then use SOS: `!analyze -v`, `!clrstack`, `!pe`\n\n**3. LLDB + SOS** (Linux/macOS):\n```bash\nlldb --core your-file.dmp\nplugin load libsosplugin.so\nsos PrintException\n```\n\n**Typical workflow:**\n1. Run `pe` (print exception) to see the exception that caused the crash\n2. Run `clrstack` to see the call stack at the point of failure\n3. Inspect locals/objects with `dumpobj` if needed\n\nWould you like help with a specific step, or do you want me to run `dotnet-dump analyze` on your file if it's accessible in this environment?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"bf127a32-328d-4e74-83bb-449d114827df","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about analyzing a .dmp crash dump file from a .NET application. Let me check the available skills - there's a \"dump-collect\" skill, but its description specifically says:\n\n- USE FOR: enabling automatic crash dumps, capturing dumps, setting up dump collection\n- DO NOT USE FOR: analyzing or debugging dumps, post-mortem investigation with lldb/windbg/dotnet-dump analyze\n\nSo the dump-collect skill is NOT appropriate here since the user wants to analyze a dump, not collect one.\n\nI should help the user directly with guidance on analyzing their crash dump.","outputTokens":447,"requestId":"680D:2EE789:C72819:D50030:6A0B0169"},"id":"5f0c819e-5b70-4515-a061-334fb88b3ae4","timestamp":"2026-05-18T12:09:27.184Z","parentId":"5ff3e2c6-7478-481c-9a5e-8bf3bad95c3b"}
